1
00:00:01,235 --> 00:00:03,471
Yesterday at the opening of an
event in the city,

2
00:00:03,604 --> 00:00:08,275
30 visitors reported nausea after
eating catered bento.

3
00:00:08,409 --> 00:00:10,811
They were taken to a nearby
hospital.

4
00:00:10,945 --> 00:00:14,482
The salmonella bacteria was
detected in the patients.

5
00:00:14,615 --> 00:00:19,854
The cause was expired frozen meat
used by the bento packager...

6
00:00:19,987 --> 00:00:21,222
Hayakawa-san.

7
00:00:22,723 --> 00:00:24,091
You're alone? Where's Yamagishi?

8
00:00:24,225 --> 00:00:26,060
I haven't been able to reach him.

9
00:00:26,193 --> 00:00:30,631
Figures; millennials
just don't grow up.

10
00:00:33,968 --> 00:00:35,636
Take the badge off.

11
00:00:37,004 --> 00:00:39,006
- Is Nogami-san at his office?
- Yeah.

12
00:00:41,575 --> 00:00:43,577
Oh! Hey!

13
00:00:50,384 --> 00:00:54,922
If somebody dies we're both
done for; do you realize that?

14
00:00:55,823 --> 00:00:56,757
I'm sorry.

15
00:00:57,324 --> 00:01:00,194
We couldn't find the person
in charge, so the former...

16
00:01:00,361 --> 00:01:04,632
Did Min Min market frozen meat
and side dishes only this month?

17
00:01:08,035 --> 00:01:09,203
There's also flavor-flakes...

18
00:01:09,303 --> 00:01:10,638
We're talking about the
food poisoning case;

19
00:01:10,771 --> 00:01:12,072
so flavor-flakes don't count.

20
00:01:12,306 --> 00:01:13,507
The issue here is, was the cause...

21
00:01:13,641 --> 00:01:17,278
your company's shumai
or Min Min's chicken wings?

22
00:01:17,411 --> 00:01:20,448
Both were supposedly included
in the bento yesterday.

23
00:01:20,548 --> 00:01:22,349
Chicken wings?

24
00:01:22,483 --> 00:01:25,786
If so, those were used before
the expiration date.

25
00:01:25,886 --> 00:01:28,222
Huh? What are you saying, then?

26
00:01:30,391 --> 00:01:31,859
You're saying it was our shumai?

27
00:01:31,992 --> 00:01:33,928
This is what happened,
Sakama-san...

28
00:01:34,028 --> 00:01:38,966
they didn't all fit in the freezer,
so they naturally thawed out.

29
00:01:39,066 --> 00:01:41,035
- Huh?
- I'm sorry.

30
00:01:41,101 --> 00:01:44,271
We ordered too much, double
the amount of food.

31
00:01:44,405 --> 00:01:45,739
How long's this been going on?

32
00:01:45,840 --> 00:01:48,275
I don't know, let's see...

33
00:01:48,409 --> 00:01:49,610
Hey!
Get your act together old man!

34
00:01:49,743 --> 00:01:53,013
Why did you sell food that didn't
fit in the freezer?

35
00:01:53,147 --> 00:01:57,651
Because I couldn't sever ties
with either company.

36
00:01:57,785 --> 00:01:59,854
Ai Ai and Min Min are both
faithful companies...

37
00:01:59,987 --> 00:02:01,388
You were getting
buttered up.

38
00:02:01,522 --> 00:02:06,093
I heard Min Min would take you to
"naughty" places.

39
00:02:08,129 --> 00:02:12,533
Well, there's no point in raising a
fuss. What's done is done.

40
00:02:12,633 --> 00:02:14,768
Let's talk about the future instead.

41
00:02:16,103 --> 00:02:19,406
First we must make public apology,
explain how it happened,

42
00:02:19,507 --> 00:02:21,475
and respond to the media.

43
00:02:21,609 --> 00:02:26,814
So far it's clear that the cause was
careless food maintenance.

44
00:02:26,947 --> 00:02:29,283
The media will be all over that.

45
00:02:29,383 --> 00:02:33,254
Your relationship to Min Min
goes back quite a long way.

46
00:02:33,387 --> 00:02:36,223
Yes. It goes back to the
inception of the business, so...

47
00:02:36,357 --> 00:02:38,325
it's been 23 years.

48
00:02:38,425 --> 00:02:41,729
Our company's relationship to
you is short in comparison.

49
00:02:41,862 --> 00:02:44,431
My relationship with you
started just this year;

50
00:02:44,565 --> 00:02:48,569
I heard you forced
a contract on us.

51
00:02:48,702 --> 00:02:51,906
We are merely newcomers.

52
00:02:52,840 --> 00:02:55,442
What is it you're trying to say?

53
00:02:56,577 --> 00:02:58,712
To be clear...

54
00:02:58,846 --> 00:03:05,119
our request to you is to not
mention the name of our company.

55
00:03:05,219 --> 00:03:06,520
He's direct.

56
00:03:06,654 --> 00:03:10,057
Excuse me, but we're a
major business.

57
00:03:10,190 --> 00:03:11,325
We have an image to protect.

58
00:03:11,425 --> 00:03:14,662
Of course, I'm not asking you
to do us this favor for free.

59
00:03:15,296 --> 00:03:16,630
Nogami-san.

60
00:03:16,964 --> 00:03:19,300
How much do you currently
owe us?

61
00:03:19,433 --> 00:03:23,671
How much? Well... I haven't
even made a single payment yet.

62
00:03:23,804 --> 00:03:25,339
Approximately 3 million yen.

63
00:03:26,507 --> 00:03:31,011
Our company will not bill you
a penny of it.

64
00:03:33,447 --> 00:03:39,053
Your lawsuit and compensations
to victims will be quite heavy.

65
00:03:39,186 --> 00:03:43,657
It's best if you cut as many
corners as you can.

66
00:03:43,757 --> 00:03:47,061
Shouldn't we find out first if the
culprit was the wing or shumai?

67
00:03:47,194 --> 00:03:48,662
It wasn't us!

68
00:03:49,029 --> 00:03:50,431
We didn't deliver a supply.

69
00:03:54,935 --> 00:03:57,004
Oh man...

70
00:03:58,072 --> 00:04:00,908
this is so soothing...

71
00:04:22,563 --> 00:04:27,034
We're Millennials.
Got a Problem?

72
00:04:28,569 --> 00:04:31,338
"What are you going to do?"
he asked. That young punk!

73
00:04:31,472 --> 00:04:34,008
He jumped ship real fast.

74
00:04:34,108 --> 00:04:38,112
3 million must be a drop in the
bucket for a major corporation.

75
00:04:38,245 --> 00:04:39,947
How much were <i>we</i> owed?

76
00:04:40,014 --> 00:04:42,282
-Let's see...
- It doesn't matter!

77
00:04:42,383 --> 00:04:44,018
We can't afford to
waive debts owed to us.

78
00:04:44,151 --> 00:04:45,452
I'm sorry.

79
00:04:49,356 --> 00:04:50,824
Come with me.

80
00:04:51,325 --> 00:04:52,326
Yes.

81
00:04:58,799 --> 00:05:01,568
All right, all right.

82
00:05:01,702 --> 00:05:03,971
Come and get it.

83
00:05:04,071 --> 00:05:06,173
Okay.

84
00:05:06,306 --> 00:05:09,176
Hey, hey, hey, hey.

85
00:05:10,444 --> 00:05:11,812
Oh. I'm sorry.

86
00:05:12,279 --> 00:05:13,280
I'm sorry.

87
00:05:15,049 --> 00:05:17,785
Hey! There!

88
00:05:20,888 --> 00:05:22,222
Argh!

89
00:05:24,224 --> 00:05:25,392
Don't mess with me!

90
00:05:25,526 --> 00:05:26,527
I'm sorry.

91
00:05:26,660 --> 00:05:28,662
- Don't mess with me!
- Okay, I'm sorry.

92
00:05:28,762 --> 00:05:30,431
Okay.

93
00:05:30,564 --> 00:05:32,433
Don't mess with me.

94
00:05:34,968 --> 00:05:36,370
Damn it!

95
00:05:54,855 --> 00:05:56,557
I feel better now.

96
00:05:56,690 --> 00:05:57,558
Really?

97
00:05:57,691 --> 00:05:59,026
Of course not!

98
00:05:59,159 --> 00:06:00,260
I'm sorry.

99
00:06:04,298 --> 00:06:05,399
That Nogami-san...

100
00:06:06,233 --> 00:06:08,235
what'll he do after
losing his connections?

101
00:06:08,602 --> 00:06:11,438
Under normal circumstances he'd
take the blame and get fired.

102
00:06:11,572 --> 00:06:12,339
Huh?

103
00:06:12,473 --> 00:06:17,010
The penalty is severe on
the mishandling of food.

104
00:06:17,811 --> 00:06:21,115
His excuse was the supply thawed
because it didn't fit the freezer.

105
00:06:21,215 --> 00:06:22,516
Sounds like my wife.

106
00:06:24,451 --> 00:06:25,452
I sort of...

107
00:06:27,354 --> 00:06:28,856
feel responsible.

108
00:06:31,024 --> 00:06:32,025
That time...

109
00:06:32,926 --> 00:06:34,895
had I listened to Yamagishi
and pulled us out...

110
00:06:35,028 --> 00:06:37,631
"...this wouldn't have happened";
is that what you're saying?

111
00:06:38,398 --> 00:06:40,634
I didn't want to let them
usurp our business...

112
00:06:41,401 --> 00:06:42,970
and I, personally...

113
00:06:43,070 --> 00:06:46,006
wanted a feather in my cap before
returning to business management.

114
00:06:46,140 --> 00:06:47,741
Then my girlfriend got transferred,

115
00:06:47,841 --> 00:06:49,843
There were so many things
happening...

116
00:06:50,778 --> 00:06:52,646
I panicked and did things
I'd usually never do.

117
00:06:54,047 --> 00:06:55,849
As a result I've hurt not only

118
00:06:56,216 --> 00:06:58,218
Nogami-san, but also our
company's name.

119
00:07:03,357 --> 00:07:05,325
Let's go the opposite direction.

120
00:07:05,425 --> 00:07:06,393
Opposite direction?

121
00:07:07,528 --> 00:07:10,430
You have trusted us...

122
00:07:11,098 --> 00:07:12,599
no, no, no...

123
00:07:13,567 --> 00:07:15,035
at this time...

124
00:07:16,003 --> 00:07:19,773
although you had entrusted
in our company...

125
00:07:19,907 --> 00:07:24,578
no, no... we were the grateful
recipients of your trust...

126
00:07:24,678 --> 00:07:27,881
trust... uh... trust...

127
00:07:28,015 --> 00:07:29,449
Our trusting customers...

128
00:07:29,550 --> 00:07:32,653
we have betrayed them.

129
00:07:32,786 --> 00:07:35,022
And of that we deeply express
our apology.

130
00:07:35,989 --> 00:07:37,224
We are very...

131
00:07:37,991 --> 00:07:41,595
very sorry.

132
00:07:41,728 --> 00:07:42,930
Very...

133
00:07:54,441 --> 00:07:57,077
We are paying a portion of the
lawsuit and compensation fees.

134
00:07:57,177 --> 00:07:59,146
But we needn't.
We weren't in the wrong.

135
00:07:59,279 --> 00:08:02,149
Paying though we weren't in the
wrong will improve our image.

136
00:08:02,282 --> 00:08:06,220
Truly. This will guarantee an
exclusive contract with us alone.

137
00:08:06,353 --> 00:08:08,655
Because Ai Ai Foods is
out the picture now.

138
00:08:09,323 --> 00:08:10,090
But still ...

139
00:08:10,224 --> 00:08:11,491
it's a sinking ship.

140
00:08:11,592 --> 00:08:13,193
Nogami is in a desperate situation.

141
00:08:13,327 --> 00:08:15,395
That's why we rescue him, and he
becomes indebted to us.

142
00:08:15,529 --> 00:08:16,430
This isn't goodwill.

143
00:08:16,563 --> 00:08:19,433
It's business. We need him
to recover or it's a bust.

144
00:08:19,566 --> 00:08:22,035
Sakama! Keep a close
watch on Nogami.

145
00:08:22,135 --> 00:08:24,004
His back's against the wall...

146
00:08:24,104 --> 00:08:25,639
There's no telling what he'll do.

147
00:08:26,974 --> 00:08:28,575
And about Yamagishi...

148
00:08:28,675 --> 00:08:30,844
when you reach him, tell him
to write a letter of apology.

149
00:08:33,013 --> 00:08:34,448
Awesome.

150
00:08:35,349 --> 00:08:37,117
I've never seen Hayakawa-san
in-action before.

151
00:08:37,217 --> 00:08:40,020
He's a legendary businessman
in spite of how he looks.

152
00:08:41,855 --> 00:08:43,857
Compared to him I'm just...

153
00:08:44,224 --> 00:08:46,226
slow witted...

154
00:08:46,360 --> 00:08:48,161
all I ever do is
exercise hindsight...

155
00:08:48,262 --> 00:08:51,231
At least you self-reflect, which
can't be said of Yamagishi.

156
00:08:53,934 --> 00:08:58,238
Why is this the only
way I can talk?

157
00:08:58,338 --> 00:08:59,406
What?

158
00:08:59,506 --> 00:09:01,408
Oh, nothing.

159
00:09:05,445 --> 00:09:07,014
What shall we do about my dad?

160
00:09:07,114 --> 00:09:08,815
I am Miyashita Akane's father.

161
00:09:08,949 --> 00:09:10,817
You haven't told him
we've broken up?

162
00:09:10,951 --> 00:09:12,653
He wouldn't have come
if I had told him.

163
00:09:13,720 --> 00:09:15,222
Can I bring him to the
restaurant at 7:00?

164
00:09:16,857 --> 00:09:18,025
Yes.

165
00:09:18,091 --> 00:09:19,226
Ouch!

166
00:09:19,359 --> 00:09:21,028
Don't sigh!

167
00:09:24,798 --> 00:09:26,934
Here's the special skewered
assortment of poultry.

168
00:09:27,034 --> 00:09:29,903
- This is quite a good restaurant.
- Thank you very much.

169
00:09:30,003 --> 00:09:32,906
Maybe they're still going out.

170
00:09:33,006 --> 00:09:36,310
Who's the superior, the area
manager or the store manager?

171
00:09:36,443 --> 00:09:38,278
Of course that would be
Miyashita-san.

172
00:09:38,378 --> 00:09:40,013
In that case, area manager...

173
00:09:40,147 --> 00:09:41,949
may I buy the store manager
another drink?

174
00:09:42,015 --> 00:09:44,384
You don't have to ask my
permission.

175
00:09:44,985 --> 00:09:46,019
Ah yes.

176
00:09:46,720 --> 00:09:48,655
Go on, have a seat.

177
00:09:48,755 --> 00:09:49,923
We don't have a glass. Hey...

178
00:09:50,023 --> 00:09:51,091
He sat down.

179
00:09:51,224 --> 00:09:53,193
He can't escape now.

180
00:09:53,493 --> 00:09:56,029
Why does he speak to you
using polite ceremony?

181
00:09:57,130 --> 00:09:59,433
Why does he call you
"Miyashita-san"?

182
00:10:00,267 --> 00:10:04,237
I'm his superior. He can't call
me "Akane-chan", can he?

183
00:10:04,338 --> 00:10:07,174
He has to use the honorific
"-san" even after marriage?

184
00:10:07,307 --> 00:10:09,142
That's pathetic.

185
00:10:09,276 --> 00:10:10,944
He kept grinning like a fool.

186
00:10:11,011 --> 00:10:12,846
I have no idea what he's thinking.

187
00:10:13,780 --> 00:10:15,549
You want to put on sweats?

188
00:10:15,682 --> 00:10:17,017
It's Masakazu's but...

189
00:10:18,285 --> 00:10:20,320
You lived together?

190
00:10:20,420 --> 00:10:23,223
No. He lives far away, he stayed
when he missed the last train.

191
00:10:23,357 --> 00:10:25,726
What the heck is that?

192
00:10:26,159 --> 00:10:28,929
I don't like the way he
responds to my questions.

193
00:10:29,029 --> 00:10:30,964
Are you the second son,
Masakazu-kun?

194
00:10:31,064 --> 00:10:33,433
That is so. So, so, so.

195
00:10:33,567 --> 00:10:35,736
"So, so, so, so."

196
00:10:35,869 --> 00:10:36,636
Was he telling me to die?

197
00:10:36,770 --> 00:10:39,339
He wasn't making a
pun about death.

198
00:10:39,473 --> 00:10:40,307
He was nervous.

199
00:10:40,440 --> 00:10:42,242
And then...

200
00:10:42,342 --> 00:10:44,644
he fiddled with his cell phone
during our conversation.

201
00:10:44,778 --> 00:10:49,483
If I have to be in Yurakucho at 10,
I should leave the apartment at 9.

202
00:10:49,616 --> 00:10:52,819
A friend from my townhall days will
be at the local-products exhibit...

203
00:10:52,953 --> 00:10:55,655
Get on the train to Ikebukuro
at 9:28,

204
00:10:55,756 --> 00:10:57,424
then change to the JR at
Tokyo Station.

205
00:10:57,724 --> 00:10:58,525
Oh, sure.

206
00:10:58,658 --> 00:11:03,296
Wait, the Yurakucho Line from
Akasaka-mitsuke is 2 minutes faster.

207
00:11:03,430 --> 00:11:04,931
Please board the rearmost car.

208
00:11:05,032 --> 00:11:08,435
Wait, the Ginza Line comes
a minute later...

209
00:11:08,568 --> 00:11:12,172
Wait, if you got off at Hibiya and
walked at 15km per hour...

210
00:11:12,305 --> 00:11:15,742
I can't walk at 15km per hour.

211
00:11:15,842 --> 00:11:18,245
Dad, are you lonesome,
on your own?

212
00:11:19,012 --> 00:11:20,013
Me?

213
00:11:20,113 --> 00:11:21,848
You talk a lot.

214
00:11:22,149 --> 00:11:24,451
Don't you have friends to talk
to in Saga?

215
00:11:24,551 --> 00:11:26,019
Of course I do.

216
00:11:27,654 --> 00:11:29,856
Kazushi comes home
on weekends too.

217
00:11:31,024 --> 00:11:33,427
Anyway...

218
00:11:33,860 --> 00:11:35,896
no matter what you do...

219
00:11:37,130 --> 00:11:38,865
it won't last long.

220
00:11:40,100 --> 00:11:43,303
Sleep on the futon.

221
00:11:43,437 --> 00:11:46,306
I have to drive the school
bus in the morning.

222
00:11:46,440 --> 00:11:48,675
What? You're still
doing that?

223
00:11:48,809 --> 00:11:50,077
You better quit.
It's dangerous.

224
00:11:50,177 --> 00:11:51,945
Voicing your concern?

225
00:11:52,012 --> 00:11:54,481
The elderly are sensitively aware of
when they're being treated as old.

226
00:11:54,614 --> 00:11:56,950
Young people wouldn't understand.

227
00:11:57,117 --> 00:11:59,052
We elderly get treated like so.

228
00:11:59,219 --> 00:12:01,988
So all we ever say are
elderly stuff.

229
00:12:07,160 --> 00:12:08,795
What are you doing there?

230
00:12:09,196 --> 00:12:10,030
Oh...

231
00:12:10,097 --> 00:12:12,032
"Grave of Tanoguchi household"

232
00:12:12,099 --> 00:12:14,267
I called Tanoguchi-san.

233
00:12:14,401 --> 00:12:16,236
I told her you might be going
there, so I asked her to call me.

234
00:12:17,971 --> 00:12:19,840
She said she's thinking of
moving soon...

235
00:12:20,574 --> 00:12:22,309
since the forty-nine days of
mourning have passed.

236
00:12:24,578 --> 00:12:25,645
I see.

237
00:12:27,614 --> 00:12:29,049
Time passed so fast.

238
00:12:36,823 --> 00:12:39,025
I watched the press
conference on TV.

239
00:12:39,092 --> 00:12:41,027
You should've been there
in person.

240
00:12:43,964 --> 00:12:45,465
She scolded me.

241
00:12:45,966 --> 00:12:48,702
I don't want you coming
here all the time.

242
00:12:50,137 --> 00:12:52,906
Sure, I think of you like
a son, but...

243
00:12:54,741 --> 00:12:56,643
you're not my son.

244
00:12:59,946 --> 00:13:01,214
I'm sorry.

245
00:13:02,182 --> 00:13:05,852
The way you habitually pout like
that, you're just like Hiroyuki.

246
00:13:07,187 --> 00:13:08,588
You really should...

247
00:13:09,089 --> 00:13:11,825
openly display your
shortcomings...

248
00:13:11,925 --> 00:13:14,327
entrust yourself to the
people at the office.

249
00:13:17,130 --> 00:13:18,732
The fish!

250
00:13:21,034 --> 00:13:22,235
Well...

251
00:13:22,869 --> 00:13:27,440
I really can't do that. I've already
given them an initial impression.

252
00:13:27,574 --> 00:13:30,477
You disappeared twice on them,
think about it.

253
00:13:31,845 --> 00:13:35,715
For you kids, "you can do it
if you try" is a myth.

254
00:13:35,849 --> 00:13:38,018
You kids "can't do it
if you don't try."

255
00:13:42,389 --> 00:13:43,590
So...

