- What?

522
00:27:37,056 --> 00:27:38,991
You are?

523
00:27:39,091 --> 00:27:42,862
I better keep my trap shut.

524
00:27:43,062 --> 00:27:44,263
Hey.

525
00:27:44,397 --> 00:27:45,197
But Miyashita-san...

526
00:27:45,297 --> 00:27:47,366
- Hasn't broken up!
- Welcome.

527
00:27:47,466 --> 00:27:49,602
Let me ask you something...

528
00:27:50,102 --> 00:27:51,270
to you guys...

529
00:27:51,404 --> 00:27:53,906
the millennials generation,
our hard-nosed generation is...

530
00:27:54,006 --> 00:27:55,007
repellent?

531
00:27:55,141 --> 00:27:57,343
Excuse me, but I didn't
understand that last part.

532
00:27:57,643 --> 00:28:00,146
Geezers like us that don't know

533
00:28:00,212 --> 00:28:03,049
Wikipedia and gigabytes...
are we repellent?

534
00:28:04,550 --> 00:28:06,452
All I know is "Wikipedia"
and "gigabytes".

535
00:28:06,552 --> 00:28:07,553
We're repellent.

536
00:28:07,686 --> 00:28:09,388
In other words, we're repulsive.

537
00:28:09,822 --> 00:28:10,990
Hey.

538
00:28:11,190 --> 00:28:12,158
You from Kyushu?

539
00:28:12,224 --> 00:28:13,426
Yeah, from Kurume.

540
00:28:13,559 --> 00:28:14,994
Wow.

541
00:28:15,094 --> 00:28:16,662
I'm from Tosu of Saga.
We're neighbors.

542
00:28:16,762 --> 00:28:17,730
Really?

543
00:28:17,863 --> 00:28:19,298
Saga, huh?

544
00:28:19,432 --> 00:28:20,800
What do you want to drink?

545
00:28:20,933 --> 00:28:23,202
I'll get you shochu.
Potato liquor.

546
00:28:23,269 --> 00:28:24,770
Delicious potato.

547
00:28:45,291 --> 00:28:46,859
- Chest...
- That's enough.

548
00:28:46,992 --> 00:28:48,027
Hey.

549
00:28:48,794 --> 00:28:50,362
What's the idea?

550
00:28:50,763 --> 00:28:52,665
This is a public place.

551
00:28:52,798 --> 00:28:54,533
Yelling out loud...

552
00:28:54,733 --> 00:28:57,002
"chest, chest"...

553
00:28:58,737 --> 00:29:01,440
There are those who have
issues with that.

554
00:29:02,675 --> 00:29:05,377
There are those who
are bothered by that.

555
00:29:05,511 --> 00:29:06,579
Sorry.

556
00:29:06,879 --> 00:29:07,847
Sorry.

557
00:29:08,380 --> 00:29:09,348
Sorry.

558
00:29:15,821 --> 00:29:18,324
I'm losing it...

559
00:29:34,507 --> 00:29:36,008
I'm done for today.

560
00:29:36,575 --> 00:29:37,443
Huh?

561
00:29:39,178 --> 00:29:40,112
Okay.

562
00:29:43,916 --> 00:29:45,251
Good job today.

563
00:29:48,988 --> 00:29:50,689
They're here.

564
00:29:51,290 --> 00:29:52,458
Mother.

565
00:29:52,558 --> 00:29:53,692
Mother.

566
00:29:53,793 --> 00:29:56,295
Hurry, hurry.

567
00:29:58,531 --> 00:29:59,465
Well, well.

568
00:29:59,565 --> 00:30:02,801
Thank you for coming
such long distance.

569
00:30:02,935 --> 00:30:05,504
I am the father of
Miyashita Akane.

570
00:30:05,638 --> 00:30:07,540
I am Sakama Masakazu's
mother.

571
00:30:07,673 --> 00:30:08,641
I am Sakama...

572
00:30:08,774 --> 00:30:10,376
- Masakazu's older brother.
- Please come in.

573
00:30:10,476 --> 00:30:11,944
- Thank you.
- This way please.

574
00:30:13,479 --> 00:30:14,480
This way.

575
00:30:18,384 --> 00:30:21,187
Man, I overslept.

576
00:30:21,320 --> 00:30:22,721
When were they coming?

577
00:30:22,855 --> 00:30:23,756
Idiot.

578
00:30:24,423 --> 00:30:26,058
That's my younger sister,
Yutori.

579
00:30:28,294 --> 00:30:30,429
I didn't put on makeup yet,
I'm sorry.

580
00:30:30,529 --> 00:30:32,832
"Condolences: Miyashita"

581
00:30:40,706 --> 00:30:42,675
Oh my. I was holding my breath.

582
00:30:42,808 --> 00:30:45,611
I know I shouldn't
be so tense.

583
00:30:45,711 --> 00:30:47,646
How silly of me.

584
00:30:50,082 --> 00:30:52,918
Are the older brother and wife

585
00:30:53,052 --> 00:30:54,486
- in charge of the distillery now?
- Yes.

586
00:30:54,553 --> 00:30:55,754
Not even half a year has
gone by since we took charge.

587
00:30:55,888 --> 00:30:56,822
We're very busy.

588
00:30:56,922 --> 00:30:58,524
The distillery...

589
00:30:58,691 --> 00:31:02,228
is always the busiest
from October to March.

590
00:31:02,361 --> 00:31:04,530
My husband was meticulous.

591
00:31:04,763 --> 00:31:06,232
He thoroughly trained the
workers

592
00:31:06,365 --> 00:31:08,500
to distill new wine.

593
00:31:09,468 --> 00:31:11,170
And after that was done...

594
00:31:12,304 --> 00:31:14,406
he passed away in March.

595
00:31:15,541 --> 00:31:16,809
I see.

596
00:31:17,943 --> 00:31:18,777
Yes.

597
00:31:23,916 --> 00:31:26,518
Oh no. Silence again.

598
00:31:26,852 --> 00:31:28,487
We should talk about
cheerful things.

599
00:31:28,587 --> 00:31:30,723
I know. Why don't you
show him the storage room?

600
00:31:30,856 --> 00:31:31,624
Oh yes.

601
00:31:31,757 --> 00:31:33,192
A social science class is coming
at noon for a tour...

602
00:31:33,292 --> 00:31:35,294
I didn't come here on a social-
science tour.

603
00:31:35,427 --> 00:31:37,196
Dad. You're being rude.

604
00:31:38,030 --> 00:31:40,499
My youngest daughter Yutori
from next year is...

605
00:31:40,633 --> 00:31:43,602
I didn't come here for
frivolous banter either.

606
00:31:44,303 --> 00:31:46,805
I apologize. This is
how he talks.

607
00:31:49,375 --> 00:31:50,442
I think it was...

608
00:31:50,509 --> 00:31:52,778
in January the year before last.

609
00:31:53,712 --> 00:31:55,014
She told me she was

610
00:31:55,147 --> 00:31:57,583
seeing a man she was
intending to marry.

611
00:31:58,150 --> 00:31:59,685
It's been two-and-a-half
years since then.

612
00:31:59,818 --> 00:32:02,154
She's of good age now
to get married, and yet...

613
00:32:02,254 --> 00:32:04,056
she's been too busy with work,

614
00:32:04,189 --> 00:32:06,091
and nothing further developed.

615
00:32:06,792 --> 00:32:07,926
I was never introduced to him.

616
00:32:09,595 --> 00:32:11,797
I'm from the old world.

617
00:32:12,298 --> 00:32:15,100
Therefore I believe that
girls, when they marry,

618
00:32:15,234 --> 00:32:16,735
I mean, "women"...

619
00:32:16,835 --> 00:32:19,238
should become
part of a household.

620
00:32:20,539 --> 00:32:23,042
This has nothing to do with job
superiors and subordinates.

621
00:32:23,175 --> 00:32:24,843
Nothing to do with wages
being higher or lower.

622
00:32:24,977 --> 00:32:26,378
Those are separate issues.

623
00:32:26,779 --> 00:32:29,048
A man must shoulder
responsibility.

624
00:32:30,416 --> 00:32:33,485
I hope Masakazu-kun
has the will to do so.

625
00:32:33,552 --> 00:32:35,554
Well of course.

626
00:32:35,688 --> 00:32:37,890
Isn't that so?
That's his intention.

627
00:32:40,459 --> 00:32:42,394
Bro's ears are bright red.

628
00:32:42,761 --> 00:32:44,530
Yutori-chan.

629
00:32:45,431 --> 00:32:48,667
I'm not expecting
an immediate reply.

630
00:32:48,901 --> 00:32:49,668
- Missus.
- Yes?

631
00:32:49,802 --> 00:32:50,836
May I borrow a
brush-pen?

632
00:32:50,969 --> 00:32:52,438
A brush-pen?

633
00:32:52,504 --> 00:32:54,306
Brush-pen... brush-pen...

634
00:32:56,475 --> 00:32:58,010
What are you up to?

635
00:32:58,143 --> 00:32:59,878
Oh, I bought this

636
00:33:00,012 --> 00:33:01,647
gift yesterday

637
00:33:01,780 --> 00:33:02,948
at a department store.

638
00:33:03,048 --> 00:33:04,883
It's a little too soon...

639
00:33:05,017 --> 00:33:07,419
What do you mean?
It's not too soon.

640
00:33:07,720 --> 00:33:09,555
Because, like you said...

641
00:33:09,688 --> 00:33:11,423
he hasn't given
you a reply yet.

642
00:33:11,590 --> 00:33:13,425
Oh yeah.

643
00:33:13,525 --> 00:33:14,893
I'll take the brush-pen,

644
00:33:15,027 --> 00:33:16,628
and write this and that
in the registry.

645
00:33:16,762 --> 00:33:18,364
You can think about
it while I do that.

646
00:33:18,464 --> 00:33:20,132
- Brush-pen.
- Yes.

647
00:33:20,265 --> 00:33:21,667
Oh no, I gave it to him.

648
00:33:21,800 --> 00:33:23,168
Hey, just a second.

649
00:33:23,302 --> 00:33:25,337
Relax, dad.

650
00:33:25,471 --> 00:33:26,972
You're jumping the gun.

651
00:33:27,606 --> 00:33:29,942
Besides, the situation is
reversed to begin with.

652
00:33:30,042 --> 00:33:32,344
The groom's family is
supposed to make the preparation.

653
00:33:32,611 --> 00:33:33,679
- What?
- Yes.

654
00:33:34,446 --> 00:33:36,648
This is all because you're
uncommitted...

655
00:33:36,749 --> 00:33:39,151
That's right, Masakazu.

656
00:33:39,251 --> 00:33:40,486
What are your thoughts?

657
00:33:41,387 --> 00:33:43,322
Say something.

658
00:33:56,668 --> 00:33:58,003
I do love...

659
00:33:59,671 --> 00:34:00,639
Akane-san.

660
00:34:07,679 --> 00:34:08,614
However...

661
00:34:10,349 --> 00:34:11,683
I hate her father.

662
00:34:11,817 --> 00:34:12,818
Idiot!

663
00:34:13,152 --> 00:34:14,319
Because he...

664
00:34:14,586 --> 00:34:15,988
barges in all of a sudden...

665
00:34:16,088 --> 00:34:18,056
He asks about my family,
he asks about my siblings,

666
00:34:18,190 --> 00:34:19,858
he asks about my work; but he
asks nothing about me.

667
00:34:20,359 --> 00:34:21,627
What kind of person am I?

668
00:34:21,760 --> 00:34:24,129
What are my thoughts? Those
things don't matter at all to you?

669
00:34:24,863 --> 00:34:26,298
I'm the one getting married here.

670
00:34:26,799 --> 00:34:28,333
My family, siblings, work,

671
00:34:28,467 --> 00:34:29,968
my surroundings got
nothing to do with it.

672
00:34:30,502 --> 00:34:31,770
Furthermore...

673
00:34:31,904 --> 00:34:33,505
you don't ask about your
daughter's feelings...

674
00:34:33,639 --> 00:34:35,107
what are her concerns?

675
00:34:35,207 --> 00:34:38,043
Yet you tell her to choose work or
marriage, just because she's of age.

676
00:34:39,144 --> 00:34:40,345
I don't get it.

677
00:34:41,447 --> 00:34:42,548
But that, you see...

678
00:34:42,681 --> 00:34:44,483
unless the both of you
get fully committed...

679
00:34:44,583 --> 00:34:46,418
things won't move forward.

680
00:34:46,518 --> 00:34:48,187
Of course it won't move forward.

681
00:34:50,923 --> 00:34:52,291
Because we're not a couple.

682
00:34:53,091 --> 00:34:54,593
What are you talking about?

683
00:34:56,295 --> 00:34:57,362
I'm sorry.

684
00:35:00,265 --> 00:35:01,600
We have broken up.

685
00:35:04,470 --> 00:35:06,438
- Is that true?
- Yes.

686
00:35:07,439 --> 00:35:08,507
I'm sorry.

687
00:35:10,342 --> 00:35:11,376
What?

688
00:35:11,677 --> 00:35:12,978
In that case...

689
00:35:13,111 --> 00:35:14,279
what are we doing here?

690
00:35:14,379 --> 00:35:16,248
We're no longer a couple
so I'll go ahead and say it...

691
00:35:17,049 --> 00:35:19,151
Miyashita-san was given a
promotion and transfer.

692
00:35:19,918 --> 00:35:21,520
She was at a loss because
I'm the way I am.

693
00:35:21,887 --> 00:35:23,822
- That's not true.
- Let me talk.

694
00:35:25,691 --> 00:35:27,226
I got to hate myself
eventually...

695
00:35:28,393 --> 00:35:29,928
I severed my Achilles' heel...

696
00:35:30,229 --> 00:35:32,130
and finally we decided to
break up for now.

697
00:35:33,398 --> 00:35:35,734
Wrong. Totally wrong.

698
00:35:36,134 --> 00:35:38,170
I didn't want to break up.

699
00:35:40,005 --> 00:35:41,874
What are we doing here?

700
00:35:46,345 --> 00:35:48,347
I wanted to marry you.

701
00:35:49,481 --> 00:35:50,916
Whether I become a homemaker,

702
00:35:51,049 --> 00:35:52,718
or choose to continue
my career...

703
00:35:53,185 --> 00:35:55,220
I was putting the decision off
till later.

704
00:35:56,989 --> 00:35:57,956
I wanted to marry first,

705
00:35:58,090 --> 00:36:00,225
and become happy.

706
00:36:01,026 --> 00:36:02,461
I wanted to become happy,

707
00:36:02,594 --> 00:36:03,862
and...

708
00:36:04,363 --> 00:36:07,466
"Oh no, we're broke.
Who'll go to work?"

709
00:36:08,467 --> 00:36:09,902
That would have been
fine for me.

710
00:36:10,002 --> 00:36:10,903
It's not that simple.

711
00:36:11,003 --> 00:36:11,904
Why?

712
00:36:12,004 --> 00:36:13,639
It's okay for us, but...

713
00:36:14,640 --> 00:36:15,507
what about our surroundings?

714
00:36:15,641 --> 00:36:17,776
I told you I don't care
about our surroundings.

715
00:36:17,876 --> 00:36:19,044
But...

716
00:36:19,378 --> 00:36:20,379
That's why...

717
00:36:20,946 --> 00:36:22,848
that's what I'm talking about.

718
00:36:23,982 --> 00:36:25,083
Forget it.

719
00:36:26,552 --> 00:36:28,554
- Akane.
- Idiot!

720
00:36:34,026 --> 00:36:35,928
Wow...

721
00:36:36,061 --> 00:36:37,262
I had no idea this distillery

722
00:36:37,396 --> 00:36:39,298
has such a reputable history.

723
00:36:39,431 --> 00:36:40,966
Outstanding, outstanding.

724
00:36:42,334 --> 00:36:43,468
When I was kid,

725
00:36:43,769 --> 00:36:46,071
we'd play hide and seek here.
My dad yelled at us for that.

726
00:36:47,606 --> 00:36:49,675
What a nice smell it has.

727
00:36:49,975 --> 00:36:51,143
It could make you tipsy.

728
00:36:52,678 --> 00:36:53,612
Um...

729
00:36:54,212 --> 00:36:55,948
you have come such a long way...

730
00:36:56,148 --> 00:36:57,149
Oh.

731
00:36:57,416 --> 00:36:58,550
It's my fault;

732
00:36:58,684 --> 00:37:00,185
I jumped the gun.

733
00:37:00,919 --> 00:37:02,187
But anyway...

734
00:37:02,321 --> 00:37:04,723
my daughter sure
is strong willed.

735
00:37:05,190 --> 00:37:06,758
I wonder who she took after?

736
00:37:08,360 --> 00:37:10,929
I was hoping she'd look after me
in my senior days...

737
00:37:11,063 --> 00:37:12,197
but it doesn't seem likely.

738
00:37:12,798 --> 00:37:14,433
My life span will shrink.

739
00:37:28,447 --> 00:37:29,715
Oh well...

740
00:37:30,549 --> 00:37:32,150
I'll be going back alone.

741
00:37:32,684 --> 00:37:33,885
I will accompany you
to the station.

742
00:37:34,019 --> 00:37:35,554
Don't bother,
that's all right.

743
00:37:35,887 --> 00:37:38,190
I'd feel awkward,
just you and me.

744
00:37:39,391 --> 00:37:41,526
I understand.
I'm sorry.

745
00:37:42,928 --> 00:37:44,096
Masakazu-kun.

746
00:37:45,063 --> 00:37:46,798
When you young folks see

747
00:37:46,932 --> 00:37:48,300
old fogies like me,

748
00:37:48,467 --> 00:37:50,068
do you think to yourselves:
"We've won"?

749
00:37:50,669 --> 00:37:51,670
Huh?

750
00:37:51,970 --> 00:37:54,139
You must feel superior to us.

751
00:37:55,641 --> 00:37:57,542
Whenever we fogies see

752
00:37:57,676 --> 00:37:59,478
young folks, we think

753
00:37:59,611 --> 00:38:01,647
without rhyme or reason:
"We've lost"!

754
00:38:03,181 --> 00:38:04,249
Although I know

755
00:38:04,383 --> 00:38:06,752
you folks don't think in terms
of winning, but...

756
00:38:07,052 --> 00:38:07,919
we, of our own accord...

757
00:38:08,053 --> 00:38:09,855
feel inferior to you folks.

758
00:38:11,556 --> 00:38:14,526
You folks don't know anything yet.

759
00:38:15,927 --> 00:38:18,563
You don't fear what you
don't know either.

760
00:38:20,232 --> 00:38:21,566
Fear...

761
00:38:21,900 --> 00:38:23,068
it's a menacing thing.

762
00:38:23,635 --> 00:38:25,437
We elderly folk call you
the millennial generation...

763
00:38:25,637 --> 00:38:27,839
we make sweeping
generalizations

764
00:38:27,973 --> 00:38:30,108
because we fear you;

765
00:38:30,208 --> 00:38:32,444
we can't look you
straight in the face.

766
00:38:35,313 --> 00:38:36,581
The logogram of
'shame' is...

767
00:38:37,482 --> 00:38:39,384
written with 'ear'
and 'heart'.

768
00:38:41,586 --> 00:38:42,587
Back in there...

769
00:38:43,455 --> 00:38:45,924
when you were
expressing your ire to me...

770
00:38:47,059 --> 00:38:48,694
I felt shame and anger.

771
00:38:49,561 --> 00:38:51,096
My ears turned bright red.

772
00:38:52,431 --> 00:38:54,933
But since I'm young, I have to
experience humbling things;

773
00:38:55,434 --> 00:38:58,103
I have to turn my ears and heart
bright red, more and more.

774
00:39:00,572 --> 00:39:01,773
I have to. Isn't that so?

775
00:39:02,808 --> 00:39:04,376
Hm?

776
00:39:04,643 --> 00:39:05,811
No, never mind.

777
00:39:16,488 --> 00:39:18,790
In appointment of Ms.
Miyashita Akane

778
00:39:19,024 --> 00:39:21,793
on the last day of June, 2016...

779
00:39:21,927 --> 00:39:23,528
has been relieved of her
duties

780
00:39:23,628 --> 00:39:26,031
of branch-management in the
Setagaya district...

781
00:39:26,131 --> 00:39:27,065
and has been appointed

782
00:39:27,165 --> 00:39:29,134
the leader of the project

783
00:39:29,267 --> 00:39:31,002
of development of
the new Sendai branch.

784
00:39:31,770 --> 00:39:33,805
- Thank you very much.
- Do your best.

785
00:39:37,476 --> 00:39:40,011
In appointment of Mr.
Sakama Masakazu,

786
00:39:40,212 --> 00:39:41,713
he has been relieved of
duties

787
00:39:41,813 --> 00:39:43,381
of store manager
at "Tori no Tami"

788
00:39:43,515 --> 00:39:45,150
and has been appointed

789
00:39:45,250 --> 00:39:47,919
the general area manager of all
branches in the Setagaya district.

790
00:39:48,186 --> 00:39:50,789
- I'm area manager?
- That's right.

791
00:39:51,389 --> 00:39:52,958
Our business will revive.

792
00:39:53,725 --> 00:39:54,960
Thank you very much.

793
00:39:57,929 --> 00:40:00,165
Oh. Go to Koenji now.

794
00:40:05,103 --> 00:40:07,606
Everybody from the main office
is a store manager.

795
00:40:07,739 --> 00:40:10,008
But I don't know if I'll
call you that or not...

796
00:40:11,710 --> 00:40:14,012
In any case, whenever we use
the term "store manager"...

797
00:40:14,146 --> 00:40:16,648
we're actually making fun of them.

798
00:40:18,817 --> 00:40:20,552
I look forward to working
with you.

799
00:40:21,920 --> 00:40:24,756
I'm interviewing a part-timer at
4:00, so I'll train you till then.

800
00:40:25,857 --> 00:40:26,892
Yes.

801
00:40:38,103 --> 00:40:41,239
Isn't that your friend,
Yamaji-sensei?

802
00:40:42,307 --> 00:40:44,309
Excuse me! Excuse me!

803
00:40:44,442 --> 00:40:47,445
No, first you ask the customer:
"Are you hurt?"

804
00:40:48,613 --> 00:40:49,648
Are you hurt?

805
00:40:49,781 --> 00:40:51,516
What's the point of asking me?

806
00:40:52,050 --> 00:40:53,819
Never mind. Help
with the orders.

807
00:40:53,885 --> 00:40:55,020
Yes.

808
00:40:56,488 --> 00:40:57,789
Hey, Sakama, Sakama.

809
00:40:57,889 --> 00:40:59,191
Sorry I can't right now.

810
00:40:59,291 --> 00:41:00,792
Nakamori-kun, please
arrange the skewered assortment.

811
00:41:00,892 --> 00:41:02,527
One order of skewered
assortment coming up.

812
00:41:02,627 --> 00:41:03,929
- Store manager.
- Yeah.

813
00:41:04,062 --> 00:41:05,530
Um, the real store manager.

814
00:41:05,630 --> 00:41:07,465
Who cut the turnips?

815
00:41:07,599 --> 00:41:08,667
I did.

816
00:41:08,800 --> 00:41:11,069
The turnips are cut
to 2.5 cm.

817
00:41:11,169 --> 00:41:12,504
Longer, shorter...

818
00:41:12,637 --> 00:41:13,805
shorter, longer...

819
00:41:13,905 --> 00:41:15,607
super longer!

820
00:41:15,874 --> 00:41:16,842
Do it over.

821
00:41:16,975 --> 00:41:18,343
- Yes.
- Hey, hey.

822
00:41:18,877 --> 00:41:20,712
Has Maribu-kun been
around lately?

823
00:41:21,279 --> 00:41:23,515
Come to think of it, he hasn't
been here once this whole week.

824
00:41:26,251 --> 00:41:27,419
Hey, newbie.

825
00:41:27,552 --> 00:41:30,388
- Keep a firm grip on the ladder.
- I'm sorry.

826
00:41:31,489 --> 00:41:34,025
You have a weird
first name too, guy.

827
00:41:41,600 --> 00:41:42,801
Sorry about that.

828
00:41:47,639 --> 00:41:50,375
- Gardener?
- He's an apprentice or something.

829
00:41:50,642 --> 00:41:52,143
Maribu? You got
to be kidding.

830
00:41:52,277 --> 00:41:53,845
He's not kidding!

831
00:41:53,979 --> 00:41:55,947
He said he's going legit...

832
00:41:56,815 --> 00:41:59,417
he abandoned the
bar and all...

833
00:41:59,818 --> 00:42:01,820
he's not there anymore!

834
00:42:02,487 --> 00:42:03,488
What's he talking about?

835
00:42:03,588 --> 00:42:05,390
Excuse me!

836
00:42:05,523 --> 00:42:07,292
Excuse us.
Excuse us.

837
00:42:07,425 --> 00:42:08,293
Excuse us.

838
00:42:08,426 --> 00:42:09,261
Huh?

839
00:42:09,394 --> 00:42:10,729
I just heard a girl's voice.

840
00:42:10,795 --> 00:42:12,430
She's the new part-timer.

841
00:42:12,564 --> 00:42:14,099
What? Wait a sec...

842
00:42:14,232 --> 00:42:16,601
What? What is this?

843
00:42:16,735 --> 00:42:18,803
I figured I would see you
if I worked here...

844
00:42:18,937 --> 00:42:20,805
and I'd get paid hourly
wages for it.

845
00:42:21,139 --> 00:42:22,674
Store manager, will you
move out of the way?

846
00:42:22,807 --> 00:42:24,643
Excuse me...

847
00:42:24,776 --> 00:42:26,044
Really, though...

848
00:42:26,177 --> 00:42:27,178
what's going on here?

849
00:42:27,312 --> 00:42:29,648
And also, starting July,
I'm the area manager.

850
00:42:30,315 --> 00:42:32,484
So I'm telling you...

851
00:42:33,151 --> 00:42:35,720
I chose work over marriage
this time, but...

852
00:42:36,721 --> 00:42:40,425
it's not that I've
given up on marriage.

853
00:42:42,961 --> 00:42:45,530
I'm an eligible date,
believe it or not.

854
00:42:45,630 --> 00:42:47,332
Sure, sure, I understand.

855
00:42:47,732 --> 00:42:50,402
Think of it as adding to your
marriage endeavors, then.

856
00:42:50,502 --> 00:42:51,469
What?

857
00:42:51,937 --> 00:42:53,838
Going to Sendai?

858
00:42:54,139 --> 00:42:56,107
Not a bad way to look at it.

859
00:42:56,441 --> 00:42:58,677
Like Date Masamune
or something.

860
00:43:01,713 --> 00:43:03,014
Oh boy...

861
00:43:03,882 --> 00:43:05,050
my head...

862
00:43:05,183 --> 00:43:06,685
isn't banging all pistons...

863
00:43:06,818 --> 00:43:07,852
but still...

864
00:43:08,987 --> 00:43:11,089
such was my timing...

865
00:43:11,222 --> 00:43:13,058
to sever the rotten relationship.

866
00:43:13,758 --> 00:43:14,859
Sure.

867
00:43:15,226 --> 00:43:16,428
You know...

868
00:43:17,228 --> 00:43:20,465
he got promoted to
area manager...

869
00:43:20,999 --> 00:43:23,301
it's like he's got me
to thank for it.

870
00:43:23,435 --> 00:43:24,736
That's how it is.

871
00:43:24,803 --> 00:43:26,171
Yeah.

872
00:43:27,305 --> 00:43:28,640
You know...

873
00:43:28,773 --> 00:43:30,108
Yes, thank you very much.

874
00:43:35,113 --> 00:43:36,481
Excuse me.

875
00:43:36,614 --> 00:43:38,650
Oh, sorry.

876
00:43:38,850 --> 00:43:41,186
Excuse us.

877
00:43:45,457 --> 00:43:48,226
You know...

878
00:43:52,130 --> 00:43:54,132
Woops... huh?

879
00:43:55,634 --> 00:43:58,970
Am I drunk, or...

880
00:43:59,104 --> 00:44:01,439
am I trying to get drunk?

881
00:44:01,806 --> 00:44:03,208
I'm totally confused.

882
00:44:03,341 --> 00:44:05,010
Totally confused.

883
00:44:05,977 --> 00:44:07,812
Maybe you should
have a glass of water.

884
00:44:08,813 --> 00:44:11,016
Appreciate it.

885
00:44:11,149 --> 00:44:13,218
Excuse me. One
glass of water please.

886
00:44:14,419 --> 00:44:15,820
Um, Hayakawa-san.

887
00:44:17,389 --> 00:44:18,790
Don't tell me...

888
00:44:20,458 --> 00:44:21,793
What is it?

889
00:44:22,627 --> 00:44:24,129
I'm sorry.

890
00:44:30,468 --> 00:44:32,303
Hayakawa-san, are you feeling

891
00:44:32,437 --> 00:44:34,105
like it right now?

892
00:44:36,441 --> 00:44:38,109
I'm sort of feeling like it.

893
00:44:44,549 --> 00:44:46,684
Well, me too.

894
00:44:52,757 --> 00:44:55,393
If you want to pretend it was
a joke, I can go along with it.

895
00:44:55,693 --> 00:44:56,795
Now's the last chance.

896
00:44:57,295 --> 00:44:58,430
Now.

897
00:44:58,897 --> 00:45:01,733
I'm fine.

898
00:45:04,602 --> 00:45:05,637
At times like this...

899
00:45:06,438 --> 00:45:07,806
what am I supposed to say?

900
00:45:07,939 --> 00:45:09,507
A clinching one-liner?

901
00:45:12,710 --> 00:45:13,778
I know.

902
00:45:15,980 --> 00:45:17,282
"Let's take a little break here."

903
00:45:28,860 --> 00:45:31,563
You're the last, so drain the tub
after you're done.

904
00:45:35,633 --> 00:45:37,068
What if...

905
00:45:38,136 --> 00:45:39,104
Huh?

906
00:45:41,172 --> 00:45:42,474
I were to get married...

907
00:45:43,675 --> 00:45:45,677
and manage the
distillery the with you...

908
00:45:46,845 --> 00:45:47,879
What do you think?

909
00:45:49,948 --> 00:45:51,015
Never mind.

910
00:45:58,189 --> 00:45:59,524
If you're reluctant to
continue the heritage...

911
00:45:59,624 --> 00:46:00,759
I'd rather shut it down.

912
00:46:00,859 --> 00:46:01,926
Who cars about this
booze warehouse?

913
00:46:02,393 --> 00:46:03,428
Good morning,
Miyashita-kun.

914
00:46:03,561 --> 00:46:04,863
Good morning,
division chief.

915
00:46:04,963 --> 00:46:07,098
There are some things virgins
know more about.

916
00:46:07,232 --> 00:46:08,333
Maribu-san!

917
00:46:08,466 --> 00:46:09,734
What happened?

918
00:46:09,801 --> 00:46:12,237
I'm quitting my job
and getting married.

